  "prompt": "I lost my prescription slip for norco 10-325 before having filled it what can I do?",
  "response": "If you've lost your prescription slip for Norco (hydrocodone/acetaminophen) 10-325, here's what you can do:\n\n1. **Contact Your Doctor**: Reach out to the healthcare provider who prescribed the medication. They may be able to provide a replacement or a new prescription.\n\n2. **Pharmacy Inquiry**: If your doctor sent the prescription electronically to the pharmacy, the pharmacy may have a record of it. Contact them to see if they can help.\n\n3. **Medical Records**: If your prescription is part of your medical file, your doctor's office might be able to retrieve it for you.\n\n4. **Follow-Up Appointment**: If necessary, schedule an appointment with your doctor to discuss your pain management needs and obtain a new prescription.\n\n5. **Be Aware of Regulations**: Keep in mind that prescriptions for controlled substances like Norco may have specific regulations. Be prepared for potential restrictions or requirements.\n\nIt's always best to handle prescription issues as soon as possible, especially for medications that are essential for your health and well-being.",
